BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Clay Exploration Evenings: Lvl 2 — Sebastopol Center For the Art
 s\, California
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T000000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T000000
UID:94e10dfdb6da6dfdc25337dcc6cd061a@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Clay Exploration Evenings: Lvl 2\, 3/12\n\n  \n    \n      \n 
        \n          $255.00\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\nThursdays\, Marc
 h 12 - April 16\, 2026 (6 sessions) 6 - 8:30pm$210 + $45 clay fee (pre-reg
 istration required)This course is designed for students wishing to explore
  hand-building techniques at an intermediate to advanced level and delve d
 eeper into refining their clay skills. Each session will start with a demo
 nstration of a specific technique related to functional and/or decorative 
 pottery. Participants are invited to explore new ideas and to try pieces t
 hat might be of a more challenging nature. Some of what we can explore are
  freeform coil pots\, soft slab work\, hard slab technique\, a variety of 
 sculptural techniques and a sampling of the many stamping\, carving and te
 xtural surface treatments on clay. We will investigate ways to use slips a
 nd glaze that will add color to the forms we create.About the Instructor: 
 Michael Citrino has had a love affair with clay for over 50 years. After h
 is college experience at California College of Arts and Crafts with Viola 
 Frey and further work at Humboldt State University with Lew Merrick\, he r
 an a stained glass business for 18 years. Michael and his wife left for Tu
 rkey in 1991 to teach in International Schools. For 26 years he taught K-1
 2 art\, including Ceramics\, Drawing\, Photography\, Design and Sculpture 
 at schools in six different countries. He started clay programs for High S
 chool and Middle School students at three of those schools. At four of the
 se schools he offered after school and weekend ceramics sessions for teach
 ers and parents. Michael’s work ranges from the traditional to the exper
 imental and a wide swath in between. His approach to teaching is to help s
 tudents explore the playful nature of the clay room and nurture a love for
  the possibilities that medium presents. \n\n\n\n\n\n        \n          \
 n            \n              Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/clay-exploration-evenings-lvl
 -2
X-SOURCE:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
END:VEVENT
