UID:d7ed4d01f45cad4703d89ffe29ac191c@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Out of Stock\n      \n    \n\n\n\n\nSpring Bloom Watercolors\n
 \n  \n    \n      \n        \n          $170.00\n        \n      \n    \n 
  \n\nSaturday\, March 21\, 2026 10AM - 4PMCost: $130 + $40 materials feeCe
 lebrate the full arrival of spring with a day of watercolor painting inspi
 red by Sonoma County’s vibrant blooms—fresh cut California poppy\, lup
 in\, wild iris\, wild roses\, lilac\, magnolia\, daffodils\, tulips\, dwar
 f iris (Iris reticulata)\, crocus\, grape hyacinth\, and cherry\, peach\, 
 and apple blossoms.Focus on building strong compositions using color\, tex
 ture\, light\, and form\, developed through wet washes\, controlled washes
 \, and textural techniques. Guided discussions explore the essential eleme
 nts of visual art to help you create expressive\, individual work.All mate
 rials provided\, Space limited to 10 studentsDiscussion break 12:30pm. Ple
 ase bring a brown bag lunchAbout the Instructor: Lynn Zachreson studied ar
 t at the University of Minnesota and San Jose State University—Painting\
 , Printmaking: BA Fine Art. She has experience teaching all ages: Watercol
 or painting skills\, 30+ years\, Watercolor figure painting 20+ years\, an
 d Fine Art Basics with Mixed Media 20+ years. Lynn enjoys spending her tim
 e painting\, teaching\, long distance hiking\, and gardening. View Lynn’
 s art here: https://lynnzachresonart.com/\n\n\n\n\n\n        \n          \
 n            \n              Add to cart
