BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Intro to Peaceful Pottery: 03/25- 4/22\, 2026 — Sebastopol Cente
 r For the Arts\, California
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T000000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T000000
UID:5b2868c0ea32c4501328e5ce2a57dedb@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Out of Stock\n      \n    \n\n\n\n\nIntro to Peaceful Pottery:
  03/25- 4/22\, 2026\n\n  \n    \n      \n        \n          $250.00\n    
     \n      \n    \n  \n\nWednesdays\, March 25 - April 22\, 2026 (6 sessi
 ons)\; 6pm-8:30pmClass fee: $210 + Materials fee: $40Ages 16 and upAll lev
 els welcome (beginner to advanced)Intro to Throwing and HandbuildingThis i
 s a great class for those who want to enjoy building something with their 
 own hands and experience the personal benefits of working with clay. Instr
 uction will cover the basics of wheel throwing\, hand-building (slab\, coi
 l\, freeform)\, and glazing techniques. Students will also have unstructur
 ed time to work on their own creations.The class will explore the benefits
  of letting go of the need to be productive and "perfect". The main goal o
 f this course is to familiarize students with how clay rooms work and why 
 they’re a fun place to be.About the Instructor: Alice Rathjen has over 4
 0 years experience working with clay. She was a production potter for five
  years. The current focus of her “art” is the sheer pleasure of playfu
 l engagement with clay. She enjoys throwing exquisite bowls\, mugs and cup
 s and seeing them go on adventures.\n\n\n\n\n\n        \n          \n     
        \n              Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/intro-to-peaceful-pottery-03/
 25-4/22-2026
X-SOURCE:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Upcycled Journal Workshop — Sebastopol Center For the Arts\, Cal
 ifornia
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T000000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T000000
UID:390a0c2478e7262c4525db6554fd5c09@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Upcycled Journal Workshop: 03/26/26\n\n  \n    \n      \n     
    \n          $70.00\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\nThursday\, March 26\,
  2026\; 6PM-9PM$60 + $10 Materials feeA fun and creative workshop turning 
 a cereal/snack box into a unique handmade journal. Using scissors we will 
 remove parts of the boxes until we have what we will use as our cover. The
 n using miscellaneous papers we fold these into the pages of our journals.
  With simple book-binding skills using a needle and waxed thread we will s
 titch the pages into our covers. We will also decorate the covers of our j
 ournals with collage papers and/or paint.Examples of completed journals wi
 ll be shown and step by step instruction will be provided along with all s
 upplies. Short exercises to boost your creativity\, journal prompts\, and 
 a small gift from me are also included.Whether you are a beginning or seas
 oned artist/writer/crafter or just looking to try something new\, this is 
 a great way to get inspired and create something meaningful to you.About t
 he Instructor: Rendell Hourigan received a BBA in Marketing from Texas Tec
 h University\, and has pursued art for over 25 years\, focusing on sustain
 able mixed media. She has studied with artists including Chery Baird\, Jen
 ny London\, and Teri Sloat\, exploring drawing\, collage\, and soft pastel
 s. Her training includes workshops and courses in art journaling\, mosaics
 \, and mark-making. She’s exhibited work at the Sebastopol Center for th
 e Arts\, The Graton Gallery\, and her SOFA district studio. Drawn to the b
 eauty of discarded materials and passionate about recycling\, she incorpor
 ates reclaimed materials into her work and now leads art workshops to insp
 ire eco-conscious creativity in others.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\
 n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n        \n          \n            \n       
        Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/upcycled-journal-workshop-03/
 26/26
X-SOURCE:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Distant Voices: An Introduction to Asemic Writing — Sebastopol C
 enter For the Arts\, California
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T000000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T000000
UID:cbfa7af3099b1575974decb15b5ac1f1@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Distant Voices: An Introduction to Asemic Writing\n\n  \n    \
 n      \n        \n          $165.00\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\nSaturd
 ay\, March 28\, 2026\; 10am - 4pm$150 + $15 materials feeAsemic writing is
  the practice of creating artwork through marks that resemble handwriting\
 , yet carry no literal meaning or readable text. It is the word before wor
 ds form—the voice too distant to be understood—a cosmic expression wit
 hout country or dialect.We’ll begin with a slideshow exploring the depth
  and range of asemic writing. Looking at ancient scripts\, global language
 s\, symbols\, the calligraphic line\, and the work of contemporary asemic 
 artists\, we’ll expand our understanding of what is possible.From there\
 , you’ll begin your own asemic journey. These marks can infiltrate and t
 ransform your current artwork\, or stand alone as independent works of art
 .Using ink and watercolor with a variety of tools\, we’ll explore how to
  express what does not need to be said in words. My intention is to guide 
 you toward authentic marks—marks that arise from the heart and move beyo
 nd casual scribbling into something deeply felt and uniquely your own. All
  levels welcome.About the Instructor: Sherrie Lovler holds a BA in Studio 
 Art and has been teaching calligraphy and related arts for several decades
 . Well-known in the Western calligraphy community\, she has taught at inte
 rnational calligraphy conferences as well as at Ghost Ranch\, Friends of C
 alligraphy in San Francisco\, Society of Scribes in NYC\, La Romita School
  of Art in Italy\, Northern Arizona University\, O’Hanlon Center for the
  Arts\, and Sebastopol Center for the Arts. She is the author\, illustrato
 r\, and designer of "On Softer Ground: Paintings\, Poems and Calligraphy"\
 , which received a Gold Medal for Most Outstanding Book Design from the In
 dependent Publisher Book Awards. Her newest book\, "Distant Voices\," feat
 ures 31 full-color paintings and nine poems\, accompanied by an introducti
 on exploring her thoughts and creative process Sherrie exhibits her work i
 n juried shows\, solo exhibitions\, Art Trails and Art at the Source open 
 studios in Sonoma County. She enjoys teaching both online and in person. w
 ww.artandpoetry.com\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\
 n\n\n\n\n\n        \n          \n            \n              Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/distant-voices-an-introductio
 n-to-asemic-writing
X-SOURCE:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Explore Gel Plate Printing — Sebastopol Center For the Arts\, Ca
 lifornia
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T000000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T000000
UID:27330496c0eb50ab741419f0a224c01a@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Out of Stock\n      \n    \n\n\n\n\nExplore Gel Plate Printing
 \n\n  \n    \n      \n        \n          $130.00\n        \n      \n    \
 n  \n\nSaturday\, March 28\, 2026\; 11 AM – 3 PMFee: $115 + $15 material
 s feeAge: 16+ Participants: min. 8Learn to create beautiful designs on pap
 er by printing with a gel plate and acrylic paint. Mixed media artist Cath
 erine Cruz will teach you the basic skills for using this fun tool from pr
 inting textural backgrounds\, to layering colors\, and using stencils and 
 other applications. You will take home many prints that can be used for de
 signing collage\, mixed media art or greeting cards. This class is suitabl
 e for anyone wanting to learn this unique mono printing style and perfect 
 for beginners.What you’ll get from this workshop: Methods for applying p
 aint and pulling successful prints (Note: Magazine image transfer is not i
 ncluded in this class.)\, Techniques for creating intricate layered design
 s\, Creative use of mark-making tools and masks\, Strategies for combining
  techniques.A variety of papers will be provided but you are highly encour
 aged to bring your own papers to experiment on.IMPORTANT: Instructions for
  where to purchase your materials and how to prepare them is provided in t
 he attached PDF. The instructor will start the class with a demonstration 
 so please arrive a few minutes early to get set up so we can start on time
 .  We will take a short break for lunch between 12:30 and 1:00 pm so bring
  your lunch and a beverage.  About the instructor: Catherine Cruz is a Fre
 nch-American artist whose work is informed by textures and patterns create
 d by the passing of time and the effects of the natural elements on the bu
 ilt environment.  She holds a Bachelor of Science in interior design and s
 he worked in the field of architectural design and green building certific
 ation for over 25 years.  She has taught collage and mixed media workshops
  in the Bay Area and in France since 2019\, and this is her fifth year at 
 the Sebastopol Center for the Arts.  Her studio is located in Sebastopol a
 nd she participates in Art Trails Open Studios.  You may contact Catherine
  at beyouartstudio@gmail.com.  Check out Catherine’s other classes here:
   https://wwws.sebarts.org/visual-arts-classes.\n\n\n\n\n\n        \n     
      \n            \n              Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/explore-gel-plate-printing
X-SOURCE:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wabi Sabi Ink Painting: Finding Beauty in Imperfection — Sebasto
 pol Center For the Arts\, California
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T000000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260330T000000
UID:2696dd0ecde84219285c2d905f962cea@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Wabi Sabi Ink Painting: Finding Beauty in Imperfection\n\n  \n
     \n      \n        \n          $165.00\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\nS
 unday\, March 29\, 2026\; 10am - 4pm$150 + $15 materials feeStep into a cr
 eative space where intuition leads and imperfection becomes beauty. This w
 orkshop invites you to explore abstract art through both Eastern and Weste
 rn perspectives\, blending meditation\, movement\, and mark-making to crea
 te finished\, expressive paintings.Rooted in the Japanese aesthetic of wab
 i-sabi\, we will release the desire for perfection and welcome the unexpec
 ted. Discover the quiet magic that happens when ink meets water\, when ges
 tures emerge without planning\, and when the body and breath guide the bru
 sh.The session begins with gentle centering and meditation\, allowing you 
 to work from the heart and engage your whole body in the creative process.
  You will practice painting the ensō—the Zen circle that expresses whol
 eness\, presence\, movement\, and stillness. Using Asian brushes\, ink\, a
 nd watercolor\, you will create calligraphic paintings with layered accent
 s that bring depth\, atmosphere\, and emotion to your work.Open to all lev
 els. No prior experience required. Ideal for artists\, writers\, and anyon
 e seeking a mindful\, embodied approach to creativity.About the Instructor
 : Sherrie Lovler holds a BA in Studio Art and has been teaching calligraph
 y and related arts for several decades. Well-known in the Western calligra
 phy community\, she has taught at international calligraphy conferences as
  well as at Ghost Ranch\, Friends of Calligraphy in San Francisco\, Societ
 y of Scribes in NYC\, La Romita School of Art in Italy\, Northern Arizona 
 University\, O’Hanlon Center for the Arts\, and Sebastopol Center for th
 e Arts. She is the author\, illustrator\, and designer of "On Softer Groun
 d: Paintings\, Poems and Calligraphy"\, which received a Gold Medal for Mo
 st Outstanding Book Design from the Independent Publisher Book Awards. Her
  newest book\, "Distant Voices\," features 31 full-color paintings and nin
 e poems\, accompanied by an introduction exploring her thoughts and creati
 ve process Sherrie exhibits her work in juried shows\, solo exhibitions\, 
 Art Trails and Art at the Source open studios in Sonoma County. She enjoys
  teaching both online and in person. www.artandpoetry.com\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\
 n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n        \n          \n   
          \n              Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/wabi-sabi-ink-painting-findin
 g-beauty-in-imperfection
X-SOURCE:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
END:VEVENT
