SUMMARY:Jizo Peace Project: Clay Gathering — Sebastopol Center For the A
 rts\, California
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T000000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T000000
UID:8cddcba1e8f9cfec61bfaa3b9a4b38bc@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Jizo Peace Project: Clay Gathering for Remembrance and Peace\,
  April\n\n  \n    \n      \n        \n          $10.00\n        \n      \n
     \n  \n\nFriday\, April 3\, 2026\; 1:30 – 4:00pmDue to limited capaci
 ty\, we are asking for a suggested donation of $10 to confirm your attenda
 nce. Bring a copy of your receipt at check-in to Painting/Drawing Studio a
 djacent to Ceramics StudioJoin us for a monthly\, heart-centered gathering
  where we come together to create Jizo guardians out of clay—symbols of 
 compassion\, protection\, and peace. Rooted in the Buddhist tradition and 
 echoed across many cultures\, Jizo figures traditionally honor children an
 d all who have passed\, those in transition\, and those in distress.This o
 ngoing project is dedicated to remembering those lost to war\, with a spec
 ial focus now on the approximately 19\,000 children who have perished in I
 srael and Gaza in recent years. Through the simple\, meditative act of wor
 king with clay\, we create benevolent beings that will become part of publ
 ic exhibits and peace sites\, offering spaces for reflection\, mourning\, 
 and hope. Our gatherings conclude with a gentle ritual to honor the lives 
 of these children.Located in the Painting & Drawing Room. The gathering is
  open to ages 12 - adult\, and no prior clay experience is necessary—all
  clay and basic materials are supplied. Registration is required to partic
 ipate.Donations are welcome to help cover materials and expenses. More tha
 n a class\, this is a shared space of warmth and care—an opportunity to 
 tend to our own hearts while taking part in love in action.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\
 n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n        \n          \n 
