 ion: P/D RoomJoin French-American collage artist Catherine Cruz for a new 
 comprehensive collage workshop designed to to guide you through the comple
 te process of creating a finished collage on wood panel. Her hands-on proc
 ess will cover every step—from surface preparation and design to varnish
 ing and wiring.  You will learn presentation tips to give your artwork a p
 rofessional finish.  What you’ll obtain from this workshop: Reliable met
 hods for preparing your panel\, Technical information about selected art m
 aterials\, Creative ways to explore abstraction through collage\, Techniqu
 es for presenting your art.IMPORTANT: Each participant must purchase and b
 ring the following items listed in the attached PDF.  The class will begin
  with a demonstration\, so please plan to arrive early to allow time to se
 ttle in.A short lunch break will be held from 12:30 to 1:00 PM. Kindly bri
 ng your own lunch and beverage.About the instructor: Catherine Cruz is a F
 rench-American artist whose work is informed by textures and patterns crea
 ted by the passing of time and the effects of the natural elements on the 
 built environment.  She holds a Bachelor of Science in interior design and
  she worked in the field of architectural design and green building certif
 ication for over 25 years.  She has taught collage and mixed media worksho
 ps in the Bay Area and in France since 2019\, and this is her fifth year a
 t the Sebastopol Center for the Arts.  Her studio is located in Sebastopol
  and she participates in Art Trails Open Studios.  You may contact Catheri
 ne at beyouartstudio@gmail.com.  Check out Catherine’s other classes her
 e:  https://wwws.sebarts.org/visual-arts-classes.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\
